{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/animating-the-singular-value-decomposition-of-a-matrix-27f8ce1f7723", "time": 1683002364.053529, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/animating-the-singular-value-decomposition-of-a-matrix-27f8ce1f7723/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Animating the Singular Value Decomposition of a Matrix | by Andreas St\u00f6ckl | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Animating the Singular Value Decomposition of a Matrix", "description": "The Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) is a calculation that occurs in many applications and decomposes a matrix into the product of 3 matrices. It is used for example in the following areas: In this\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.autodesk.com/products/maya/overview", "anchor_text": "https://www.autodesk.com/products/maya/overview", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/routines.linalg.html", "anchor_text": "https://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/routines.linalg.html", "paragraph_index": 10}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rotation_matrix", "anchor_text": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rotation_matrix", "paragraph_index": 11}, {"url": "http://www.stoeckl.ai/profil/", "anchor_text": "http://www.stoeckl.ai/profil/", "paragraph_index": 17}], "all_paragraphs": ["The Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) is a calculation that occurs in many applications and decomposes a matrix into the product of 3 matrices. It is used for example in the following areas:", "In this article, I would like to show the geometrical interpretation behind this decomposition with the help of 3D animations to encourage intuition.", "You can find a good introduction to the SVD below:", "The considered (data) matrix can have any dimension of n rows and m columns, and the entries in the matrix can stand for pixel values of images, word frequencies in texts, ratings from users to movies, or many other things.", "The three matrices of the decomposition have special properties and, the linear transformation associated with the matrices, special geometric interpretations. This geometrical interpretation of the decomposition matrices I would like to show with the 3D animation.", "For illustration, I use 3x2 matrices and their decomposition products as examples to make the data presentable in 3D. A grid of small spheres is subjected to the respective linear transformations in the animation. Let us look at the result:", "To create the animations I used Autodesk Maya (https://www.autodesk.com/products/maya/overview) and used Python for scripting in Maya.", "I used a Python script to build the scene in Maya and to animate the objects. You can run the script from the script editor of Maya.", "At the start of the script, the required packages are imported. \u201cMaya.cmds\u201d to perform commands in Maya, \u201cmath\u201d for some calculations and \u201cnumpy\u201d for the Singular Value Decomposition. A box built by 3 planes is created, on which the considered spheres cast shadows.", "We set the light source and construct a grid of small spheres to test the Transformations.", "We define the transformation matrix we want to decompose and animate and calculate the matrices of the SVD with the help of the \u201cNumpy package\u201d for Linear Algebra (https://docs.scipy.org/doc/numpy/reference/routines.linalg.html).", "We need a function to perform rotations in a plane. Look at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rotation_matrix for the definition.", "And some functions to calculate the rotation axes and the rotation angle (Euler angle) for 3D rotations. See the same Wikipedia article for the definition and calculation.", "For the centers of the spheres, we use as test objects, we calculate the new coordinates after the transformations with the matrices by taking the dot product. Multiplying with matrix A leads to the same endpoints as multiplying by V, S, and U in this order.", "Finally, we construct the path for the animations of the spheres, by first rotating in a plane, then stretch the coordinates with a diagonal matrix (S) along the axes, and at the end perform a 3D rotation.", "This script was used to record the animations of several matrices with different matrix ranks. You can see the results in the video above.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "University of Applied Sciences Upper Austria / School of Informatics, Communications and Media http://www.stoeckl.ai/profil/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F27f8ce1f7723&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fanimating-the-singular-value-decomposition-of-a-matrix-27f8ce1f7723&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fanimating-the-singular-value-decomposition-of-a-matrix-27f8ce1f7723&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fanimating-the-singular-value-decomposition-of-a-matrix-27f8ce1f7723&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-